Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) help organizations measure the effectiveness of Azure operations.

Common operational KPIs include:

* Resource availability
* Incident response time
* Service uptime
* Backup success rate
* Mean Time to Recover (MTTR)
* Cost variance
* Policy compliance percentage

For example, an operations team may target a recovery time of less than thirty minutes for critical production services.

A real-life use case is management reviewing monthly KPI reports to evaluate operational improvements and identify recurring issues.

Well-defined KPIs support data-driven operational decisions.
